# ===============================================================================
# WORKFLOW_16S CREDENTIALS CONFIGURATION
# ===============================================================================
#
# This file shows example environment variables to configure credentials for
# the workflow_16s pipeline. Copy this to .env and fill in your actual values.
#
# DO NOT commit .env to version control - it contains secrets!
# Only commit .env.example with placeholder values.
#
# The precedence order for credentials is:
#   1. config.yaml (highest priority)
#   2. Environment variables (.env)
#   3. None/disabled (lowest priority, feature disabled)
#
# ===============================================================================

# ==================== USER IDENTIFIERS (OPTIONAL) ====================

# Your email address for API requests (some APIs require this for rate limiting)
# Can be institutional email for better rate limits
# EMAIL=user@institution.edu

# Email specifically for ENA (European Nucleotide Archive) API
# Falls back to EMAIL if not specified
# ENA_EMAIL=user@institution.edu

# ==================== GENOMIC/SEQUENCE DATA (OPTIONAL) ==================

# NCBI API key for enhanced rate limits (3 requests/sec with key vs 1 without)
# Get it at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/account/settings/
# NCBI_API_KEY=

# ==================== GEOSPATIAL & ENVIRONMENTAL DATA (OPTIONAL) ==================

# USGS API key for geological and hydrological data
# Get it at: https://apps.nationalmap.gov/geoprocessing/
# USGS_API_KEY=

# NREL API key for renewable energy data (solar, wind)
# Get it at: https://developer.nrel.gov/
# NREL_API_KEY=

# OpenTopography API key for DEM and topographic data
# Get it at: https://cloud.sdsc.edu/v1/AUTH_opentopography/Raster/SRTM_GL30/SRTM_GL30_srtm/
# OPENTOPOGRAPHY_API_KEY=

# ==================== ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING (OPTIONAL) ==================

# OpenAQ API key for air quality data
# Get it at: https://openaq.org/
# OPENAQ_API_KEY=

# AirNow API key for EPA air quality forecasts
# Get it at: https://docs.airnowapi.org/
# AIRNOW_API_KEY=

# MinDat API key for mineral and mining database
# Get it at: https://www.mindat.org/api.php
# MINDAT_API_KEY=

# ==================== EARTH OBSERVATION & REMOTE SENSING (OPTIONAL) ==================

# Google Earth Engine project ID
# Set this to enable satellite imagery enrichment
# Get it from: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# GOOGLE_EARTH_ENGINE_PROJECT=

# Google Earth Engine service account JSON file path
# Alternative: file path to downloaded service account JSON
# GEE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT=

# ==================== CLIMATE & MARINE DATA (OPTIONAL) ==================

# Copernicus Marine Environment Monitoring Service (CMEMS) username
# Get credentials at: https://data.marine.copernicus.eu/
# CMEMS_USERNAME=

# CMEMS password (keep this secret!)
# CMEMS_PASSWORD=

# ==================== ACADEMIC & PUBLICATION DATABASES (OPTIONAL) ==================

# Springer Nature API key for academic literature search
# Get it at: https://dev.springernature.com/
# SPRINGER_NATURE_API_KEY=

# IEEE Xplore API key for IEEE publications
# Get it at: https://developer.ieee.org/
# IEEE_XPLORE_API_KEY=

# Mendeley API key for reference management
# Get it at: https://developers.elsevier.com/
# MENDELEY_API_KEY=

# Dimensions API key for academic research metrics
# Get it at: https://app.dimensions.ai/
# DIMENSIONS_API_KEY=

# ===============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ===============================================================================
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit .env and add your credentials:
#    - Uncomment the lines you need (remove the #)
#    - Add your actual API keys after the =
#    - Leave as-is (commented out) for optional features you don't use
#
# 3. The /workflow_16s/config.yaml file is also checked first (takes precedence):
#    - You can set credentials there instead of .env
#    - But .env should be used for secrets to keep them out of version control
#
# 4. Example populated .env:
#    EMAIL=my.researcher@university.edu
#    NCBI_API_KEY=12345abcde67890
#    USGS_API_KEY=my-usgs-key
#    GOOGLE_EARTH_ENGINE_PROJECT=my-gee-project-12345
#
# 5. Test your setup:
#    python -m pytest workflow_16s/tests/test_credentials.py -v
#
# ===============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ===============================================================================
#
# - .env is in .gitignore (good - don't commit secrets!)
# - .env.example is committed (shows what's needed, no secrets)
# - Never hardcode credentials in source code
# - Use config.yaml only for development/testing
# - Use .env for production secrets
# - Rotate API keys periodically
# - Each API provider has different key rotation recommendations
#
# ===============================================================================
